                "response": "Based on my research, I have sufficient data to produce the ProspectProfile. Let me compile the findings:\n\n**Key Findings:**\n- **GitHub**: HashiCorp has 680 public repos with dominant Go (86%) language mix\n- **Top repos**: Terraform (42k stars), Vault (31.4k stars), Consul (28.7k stars) — all core IAM/infrastructure projects\n- **Tech Stack**: Primarily Go, with some Ruby, Shell, HCL\n- **Technical Contacts**: Mitchell Hashimoto (Co-founder) identified\n- **ICP Fit**: Excellent — HashiCorp is a core infrastructure/DevOps company\n\n**Tech Stack Overlap Analysis:**\nPolicyGuard (policy-as-code for IAM) aligns directly with HashiCorp's core products:\n- Vault is HashiCorp's secrets/IAM management tool\n- Terraform is their infrastructure-as-code platform\n- Consul handles service networking and identity\n- All use Go as primary language\n- All built for infrastructure automation and policy enforcement\n\n**Assessment:**\nPolicyGuard solves a direct pain point in the HashiCorp ecosystem—automating policy enforcement across their IaC/IAM tools. HashiCorp's focus on infrastructure automation and their recent emphasis on policy (Sentinel is their policy language) makes them a prime candidate. They're a mature, public company with clear DevOps/infrastructure focus.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"target_company\": \"HashiCorp\",\n  \"github_org\": \"hashicorp\",\n  \"tech_stack\": [\"Go\", \"Ruby\", \"Shell\", \"HCL\"],\n  \"top_repos\": [\n    {\"name\": \"terraform\", \"stars\": 42000, \"language\": \"Go\"},\n    {\"name\": \"vault\", \"stars\": 31400, \"language\": \"Go\"},\n    {\"name\": \"consul\", \"stars\": 28700, \"language\": \"Go\"},\n    {\"name\": \"packer\", \"stars\": 15500, \"language\": \"Go\"},\n    {\"name\": \"nomad\", \"stars\": 15100, \"language\": \"Go\"}\n  ],\n  \"contacts\": [\n    {\"name\": \"Mitchell Hashimoto\", \"role\": \"Co-founder\", \"linkedin_slug\": \"mitchellh\"}\n  ],\n  \"tech_stack_overlap_pct\": 90,\n  \"fit_score\": 92,\n  \"rationale\": \"HashiCorp is a textbook ICP match: they lead infrastructure/DevOps with Terraform, Vault, and Consul. PolicyGuard's policy-as-code automation directly complements their IAM/infrastructure platform, and their Go-heavy stack aligns with the product. They're a public, well-resourced company actively expanding policy capabilities, making them highly reachable and motivated to adopt.\"\n}\n```",
